title: National park Mavrovo
snippet: Large national park founded in 1949, featuring trails through mountains & canyons & along a river.
extensions/3: Large national park founded in 1949, featuring trails through mountains & canyons & along a river.
description: DescriptionThe Mavrovo National Park is the largest of the three national parks of North Macedonia. Located in the west of the country, it spreads over an area of about 780 km² and is characterized by deep canyons, lakes and dense forests that abound with diverse wildlife.
category: National park in the Republic of Macedonia

title: National Park „Pelister“
snippet: Covering 66 sq .mi., this popular forest of rare pines offers trails, wildlife, ski areas & views.
extensions/3: Covering 66 sq .mi., this popular forest of rare pines offers trails, wildlife, ski areas & views.
description: DescriptionPelister National Park is a national park in the Municipality of Bitola, North Macedonia. The park is located in the Baba Mountain massif and covers an area of 171.5 square kilometres. The altitude of the park varies between 927 and 2,601 m above sea level and is filled with exquisite flora and fauna.
category: National park in the Republic of Macedonia
